Where to start

Quick Start

If your business recognizes the potential of blockchain, but isn’t sure where to start, ProvLabs can help by offering a short term collaborative engagement that delivers the plan, timeline and documentation for your project. The engagement incorporate these three steps:

Business scoping

Gather key stakeholder requirements, constraints, priorities and success criteria. Information is used to develop user personas and business requirements.

Existing product evaluation

Optionally, the Quick Start includes the analysis of the existing product ecosystem, and an evaluation of blockchain-enabled integration service providers.

Product requirements

Business scoping and existing product analysis is used to construct a Product Requirements Document and Scope of Work, which includes specific solution architecture, technical deliverables, application integration, project timeline, and proposed team and costs.

SaaS and managed services - build and manage

SaaS and managed services to achieve long-term success

Operating on blockchain technology may require an on-going effort. ProvLabs will do all of the heavy lifting for you to set-up the necessary infrastructure and tooling, ensure its resiliency and code relevance, and provide client support.

A comprehensive solution to simplify the process of creating tokenized financial assets and a set of protocol-enforced governing rules for the asset. TokenLogic represents the future of asset digitization, offering an unmatched, user-friendly gateway for issuing and managing financial assets on blockchain technology.

An optional layer, BlockVault securely stores vast volumes of sensitive data linked to digital assets and transactions in an off-chain environment. Access to this data is strictly limited to authorized users through an encrypted hash code. Confidentiality is of utmost importance in the financial services sector, and BlockVault is the answer.

ProvNetis a revolutionary service to enable the configuration and management of nodes across the Provenance Blockchain Network, even within private Zones. Whether you seek to operate a query validator node or establish a private Zone on the Provenance Blockchain Network, this service streamlines the entire process.

Certain jurisdictions or aspects of your business might necessitate a private and permissioned blockchain setting. Provenance Blockchain Zones offer you this precise capability, giving you the flexibility to incorporate assets and workflows into or out of the public blockchain when it's needed. This allows you to maintain control within your defined environment while retaining the potential benefits of accessing DeFi innovations and assets outside of your Zone.

Professional services - define and build

Full breadth of capabilities

Whether you’re interested in building a new product or looking to upgrade a Web 2.0 solution to Web 3.0, ProvLabs provides end-to-end capabilities at any stage.

Business Strategy

ProvLabs will lead a collaborative process to define objectives and goals, consult on best practices and the competitive landscape, establish a business model and necessary service providers, and support the implementation to ensure results are maximized.

  • Business model
  • Strategic solution concepts

Solutioning

ProvLabs helps clients define product requirements and scope, which includes specific solution architecture, roles and responsibilities, technical deliverables, application integration, project timeline, and proposed team and costs. In this stage, we will also seek opportunities for added support of the initiative through any relevant grants.

  • Solution design
  • Solution roadmap

Development & Integration

ProvLabs helps clients across the full breadth of financial services turn their blockchain use-case into a high-value, scalable solution. Whether building from scratch or transitioning an existing solution to blockchain infrastructure, our end-to-end development services cover all stages of the development cycle.

  • Project management
  • Product build
  • Existing web 2.0 product integration
  • Integration with Provenance Blockchain

Distribution & Marketing

Bringing a product to market is just as difficult as building one. We understand those challenges and provide the end-to-end expertise to support preparations for raising capital, and taking a product to market.

  • Capital introductions
  • Pitch deck preparations
  • GTM collaboration
  • Provenance Blockchain ecosystem introductions
